>_ACT ONE_<

INT. THE COMEDY BASEMENT - BACKSTAGE - CONTINUOUS

A narrow hallway with peeling paint. Other comics mill around, checking phones, running through bits.

Maya leans against the wall, adrenaline still pumping. She pulls out her phone. Seven texts from her mom. She doesn't open them.

FRED (early 40s, Black, warmth in his eyes despite the world's weight on his shoulders) approaches. He's wearing a vintage bomber jacket and carries himself like someone who's seen things but chooses kindness anyway.

FRED
You killed out there.

MAYA
(modest)
It was okay.

FRED
Maya. I've been doing this twenty years. That wasn't okay. That was real.

Maya allows herself a small smile.

FRED (CONT'D)
