MIRIAM
No. Making people feel less alone is your job. The jokes are just how you do it.
(beat)
You're scared that if you actually succeed, you'll have to stop pretending you don't want this.

Direct hit. Maya's armor cracks just slightly.

MIRIAM (CONT'D)
(softer)
You know what I love about you?

MAYA
My devastating wit?

MIRIAM
The parts between the jokes. When you forget to perform. Like right now.

Maya's armor cracks. Just slightly.

MIRIAM (CONT'D)
I just want more of that. The real you.

MAYA
(quietly)
What if I get there and I'm still just... the diversity booking?

MIRIAM
Then you make them laugh so hard they forget they ever saw you that way.

They sit in comfortable silence, eating dumplings.

MIRIAM (CONT'D)
Want to grab coffee tomorrow? I miss you. We haven't actually hung out-hung out in like two weeks.

MAYA
I know. I'm sorry. I've just beenâ€”

MIRIAM
Hiding behind your jokes?

MAYA
(small smile)
Yeah.

MIRIAM
I can't keep waiting for you to trust me.

There's weight in that sentence. Maya hears it.

MAYA
I do trust you.

MIRIAM
Do you? Because sometimes I feel like I'm dating your performance, not... you.

MAYA
That's not fair.

MIRIAM
I know.
(softer)
