>_ACT TWO_<

EXT. THE IVORY ROOM - NIGHT

Manhattan. The club's exterior is elegantâ€”tasteful signage, velvet rope, well-dressed people in line.

Maya approaches in her best "I belong here" outfit: black jeans, white button-up, the bomber jacket. Her armor.

She stops outside. Deep breath.

MAYA
(to herself)
Read the room. Control the room. You've done this a thousand times.

She walks in.

INT. THE IVORY ROOM - CONTINUOUS

A different world from the basement clubs. Polished wood, professional lighting, a real sound system. The crowd is industry peopleâ€”agents, bookers, comedy nerds.

Maya checks in at the door. The STAGE MANAGER (efficient, kind) hands her a set list.

STAGE MANAGER
You're on in twenty. Green room's downstairs. Break a leg.

INT. THE IVORY ROOM - GREEN ROOM - CONTINUOUS

Nicer than any green room Maya's ever seen. Actual furniture. Working bathroom. Food that isn't stale chips.

Two other comics are already there, but Maya doesn't approach them. She sits apart, running through her set in her head.

The door opens. Two men in expensive suits enterâ€”out of place in a comedy club. They don't acknowledge the comics. Just walk to the back corner and start talking in low voices.

