INT. THE IVORY ROOM - STAGE - LATER

The EMCEE finishes the introduction.

EMCEE
...please welcome to The Ivory Room stage, Maya Santos!

Applause. Professional, measured.

Maya walks out. The spotlight hits her. This is it.

MAYA
Thank you! Wow, this is fancy. I usually perform in rooms where the brick is "exposed" because the landlord gave up.

Laugh. Good start.

MAYA (CONT'D)
So I was out late last night. You know, fighting crime or as my mom calls it "not giving her grandkids."

Bigger laugh. She's reading them perfectly.

MAYA (CONT'D)
People see me and they can't figure me out. Black, Filipina, queer... I'm like a diversity bingo card. 
(beat)
