then sees him: a soaking wet BLACK DOG, scraggly and eager, excitedly NUDGING HER FACE with enthusiasm completely inappropriate for this life-or-death moment.

MAYA
(whispering frantically)
Shhh! Quiet, boy!

She tries to KEEP BOSCO QUIET, PETTING HIM ON THE HEAD with shaking hands. Bosco's tail wags, spraying water everywhere.

SUIT #2 appears at the mouth of the alley. Stops. Looks left. Right.

Maya freezes, one hand still on Bosco's head. _Please don't bark. Please don't bark._

Bosco, miraculously, stays quiet. Just presses against her leg, panting softly.

Suit #2 stands there. Five seconds. Ten.

Unable to see where Maya went in the maze of boxes and shadows, he turns and heads back toward the club.

Maya doesn't move for a full thirty seconds. Just breathes. Processes.

_I'm alive._

Bosco licks her hand.

Then, as if he's done this a thousand times, Bosco TAKES OFF DOWN THE STREET.

MAYA
(whispering)
Heyâ€”waitâ€”

Bosco STOPS about half a block away, JUMPING and PAWING AT A DOOR to a small storefront. A PET STORE, dark inside.

Maya looks back toward the club. Forward at the dog.

She needs to get out of the rain. Out of view. Somewhereâ€”anywhereâ€”safe.

She QUICKLY FOLLOWS Bosco, looking over her shoulder every few steps.

EXT. PET STORE - CONTINUOUS

Maya catches up to Bosco. He's pawing at the door, tail waggingâ€”the best game ever.

Through the rain-streaked window: pet supplies in dim light. This might be his home.

She's soaked. Terrified. Out of options.

She KNOCKS ON THE DOOR and LOOKS THROUGH THE WINDOW.

MAYA
(to Bosco)
Hey, boy... is this your home?

Bosco barks once. Tail wagging.

INT. PET STORE - CONTINUOUS

A LIGHT comes on in the back.

Footsteps approach.

The door opens, revealing LARA (early 30s, Asian/Latina, intense eyes, wet hair like she was already awake, wearing dark clothes). She looks at the soaking wet woman and the soaking wet dog.

MAYA
(breathless, rushed)
Uh, hi. Does he live here? May we come in out of the rain? We are soaked.

Lara's eyes flick past Maya to the street. Scanning. Assessing.

Then back to Maya's face. Reading her.

One second of calculation.

LARA
(stepping aside)
Uh, yes. Come in, come in.

Maya practically stumbles inside. Bosco trots in like he owns the place, shaking water everywhere.

Lara closes the door. Locks it. Multiple locks. That's when Maya notices: this isn't a normal pet store.

INT. PET STORE - CONTINUOUS

The front is normal enoughâ€”shelves of pet supplies, a dusty register. But beyond the counter, Maya can see computer monitors. Equipment. This is something else.

Lara moves to a panel of screens, checking them. On the monitors: different angles of the street outside. The alley. The club entrance.

This is a surveillance operation.

MAYA
What is this place?

LARA
(still watching screens)
Pet store.

MAYA
With security cameras?

LARA
New York. Can't be too careful.

It's a lie. They both know it. But Lara's focus is on the monitors.

On one screen: SUIT #2 emerges from the club, stands under an awning, makes a phone call. His body language is tense, frustrated.

LARA (CONT'D)
(carefully)
